{
  "_what": "THE REGISTER — the completeness + quality contract for the design corpus. The autonomous mockup loop works through this recursively/iteratively and checks itself against it: every feature must be covered by >=1 view; every view must exist in each of its platform variants; every spine sequence must have a storyboard; every produced mockup must pass the quality_bar. Source of truth = the Feature & Function Inventory (real, file:line-grounded). Supersedes manifest.json as the production index.  [SINGLE REGISTRY — manifest.json was merged in here and retired to _archive/ on 2026-06-04; areas + journeys.surfaces_when folded in. All _system scripts + the gallery read THIS file.]",
  "_traceability": "Each view's `represents[]` links it to the real thing it depicts: {feature: <id from the Feature & Function Inventory>, label, code: <file:line | /api/endpoint | Suite.verb | node-type>}. The `coverage` map below is the REVERSE index (feature-id → [view-ids]) so un-mocked features are visible as gaps. feature-ids + both directions are POPULATED BY THE RUNNING AUDIT; until then represents=[] means un-grounded. See conventions.md › Traceability.",
  "design_system": "design-system.css",
  "ground_truth": "Feature & Function Inventory (from the real app).md",
  "journeys_doc": "User Journeys & UX.md",
  "quality_bar": [
    "GROUNDED — depicts only real features (no fiction). 2 node kinds (process/content) only; node statuses idle/ran/cached/stuck only; nothing shown that the app doesn't do. Build-required items (no FE yet) are LABELLED as proposed, not as existing.",
    "LINKED — represents[] lists the real features it shows, each with a code ref; the view is reachable in coverage{}.",
    "ON-SYSTEM — links ../design-system.css; uses tokens + component classes; never bespoke inline styling that belongs in the system.",
    "RESPONSIVE — reflows; resize works. Native mobile variant exists where platforms includes 'mobile' (sheets/tab-bar/thumb, not a shrunk desktop).",
    "JOURNEY-MOMENT — the mockup states which journey-step it is + when it surfaces; designed for that moment, not a loose screen.",
    "UX — attention-protecting, recognise-by-sight, RHM-as-thread, frontstage/backstage honoured.",
    "SELF-DESCRIBING — opens with a metadata comment block listing its represents[] (feature-ids + code)."
  ],
  "status_flow": "planned -> drafting -> drafted -> quality-passed -> approved(Tim). A view-variant counts DONE for the loop at quality-passed.",
  "areas": {
    "A": "The operating surface (canvas)",
    "B": "Right-hand-man + review/walkthrough organ",
    "C": "Inbox + decisions (chief-of-staff)",
    "D": "Self-build / the wire (act on outputs)",
    "E": "Models + embeddings",
    "F": "Frame, settings, system",
    "G": "Responsive system"
  },
